{"name": "Jigger & Shaker Restaurant", "phone": "013-267 7688", "lat": 2.6747209, "lng": 101.86364549999999, "review": [{"r_name": "Nyonya Kacak", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "💢 Have always been their regular customer & I will always come for their Lamb Shank. Sadly, on my latest visit the taste & quality isn’t the same anymore. Not sure if it is temporary, hoped so it is because their Lamb Shank was the best that I ever had.

💢 They have a live band while you enjoying your meal. Their staff are really helpful & very welcoming. Thank you for the great service. This place is a pork free & no lard. Muslims can come & enjoy their foods if you don’t mind they selling alcoholic beverages.", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "Richard Lee", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "Attended and helped organise my Uncle and Aunty's 70th Birthday party here on Saturday, 28th Jan 2023.  It is my 4th time organizing private events here and the crew here never failed to meet with my many requests.  They were cooperative,  tactful and professional.

I absolutely loved the Chicken Lasagna and Grilled Leg of Lamb while the rest of the spread was very tasty too.  The band Tazz & Anny (hubby n wife duo) were magnificent being able to carry some difficult folk tunes such as the 'Jingli Nona' when requested.

The set up; they were able to deliver as per requested without a hitch.  And Jasmine made changes to the type of tables and chairs meeting with our request during pre setup.

Mr Alan Kay, the Head of Hospitality and Mr Tom Lim, the Operations Manager dropped by to meet us and ask if all is well, which i thought was the icing on the cake for me as that is indeed going above and beyond.

Overall, we were very happy with all the arrangements.  At the end of the evening, we had a very happy couple!  Kudos to Jumalda, Kamarul, Jasmine & gang and the Bartender Hadi too (hope i got his name right), the Jigger's Head Chef for superbly executing the  menu for the night...    worth to mention is the Chef behind the Grill station who was so courteous.

Keep up the good work team and we'll surely be back!

Parking: Accorded reserved covered parking for private events.

Wheelchair accessibility: We had elderly that were wheelchair bound.", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "Mabel Hiew", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "Jigger & Shaker is now so different around a year ago when I last came..now the restaurant and the Clubhouse is so clean, its so happening on a friday nite, crowded with good Live Band...Food has improved, I had a glass of full bodied red wine - wonderful + Chicken Wingette & Drummet, it was so crispy n yummylicious wt the salted egg yolk dip served aside.
Well done J&S and d'Tempat Country Club mgmt & team, keep up yr good work..Dear frens, pls chk out this restaurant...u will love @ first bite..I will come again wt frens !!", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "Jacqueline Ho", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "Went on a Sunday. Live band had good voice but noisy for my taste. Only 3 tables occupied, walls surrounding, didnt enjoy "dating".

Food was disappointing. Had grilled chicken. Restaurant used breast meat it seems because it was dry and hard. Gums really hurt trying to finish the dish. Their sauce was watery. They didn't gave much sauce so had to ask for additional. Totally tasted different. Mash potatoes wasn't great either.
Also had beef lasagna. There was only 2 layers of lasagna sheets. Shocker! 1 at the bottom which was burnt to the bowl so it sticked to the bottom and i had to scrap it. Tasted hard. Basically bottom up is sheet, meat, sheet, meat and tonnes of cheese. So much cheese it overwhelmed the dish. Maybe it was the lack of the sheets too.

Sad to say, not going back. Pricey and not up to par.", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "Gwendaline Hendricks", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "On my visit at Jigger & Shaker, I really enjoyed the environment there. It was really cozy for a bar and bistro kind of concept.
The service was excellent and very professional

What we had:
Fish and chips- RM19
Comes with a large portion of crispy talapia fish, Crispy fries, coleslaw and tartar sauce on the side.

Chicken chop- RM17
A serving of fried whole chicken leg with crispy fries, coleslaw and black pepper sauce.

Hawaiian Chicken Burger with Chipotle Sauce -RM27
The burger were served a crispy chicken patty, pineapple, cheese, egg and a slice of turkey ham. With a side of mayonnaise and coleslaw and crispy fries.

Overall it was a really pleasant visit. With the view of the swimming pool while dining in and also with a friendly service given.", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "Elmo See Yap Yuong", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "Decent food. Reasonable price. Definitely love their drinks, will try next time for their cocktails. Lovely ambience with live band, not too noisy for us to have dinner there. Would say a good place for families to dine in.

The chicken boom sourdough abit too stale. Probably should serve in a bowl with slices of toasted sourdough instead would be better.", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "Joanna Low", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "Love this place! They serve good Mexican food and I would love to come back here again one day :)

Tapas: I really enjoyed all the tapas here and I really want to try the other tapas that I’ve not tried! All of their tapas taste good (as attached in the photos below) 😍 portion is big and it’s really yummy! Love their nachos! Best chicken nachos I’ve ever tried! If you love the different kinds of fries available out there, Fries Before Guys is definitely a must try ;) the Shakshuka is really good too! Thumbs up!

Pizzas: (I love how each of it has its own unique taste ☺️)
1. Smoked Duck & Peach Pizza: Sweet and savoury at the same time, duck slices and peaches and well distributed and it tasted quite nice ;)
2. Galvanize Pizza: This pizza contains prawns and eggs! Both are my fav and it’s a tomato based pizza. I love this!
3. Havana Havana Pizza: I quite like this as I’m okay with blue cheese. The blue cheese (smell and taste) is distinct in this pizza and it compliments well with the chicken breast slices and caramelised onions that’s served on this pizza :)

Love the environment and the atmosphere too :) would definitely come back again!", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "Lihbing Lau", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "Food quality has dropped since my last visit, but I am here for their live band on weekend night.
